preservation type: DEFAULT = "DRIED"; when NOT dried, specify other
ornithology definition: The integument of the bird, including skin, feathers, and some key bones and other structures (e.g., skull, bill, wing and leg bones).
notes: Note amagam of features in Uberon term links: skin = http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0002097, skull = http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0003129, bill = http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0005094, legs = http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0002103, wings = http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0000023.

ornithology definition: A museum study skin, but lacking some combination of skull, bill, legs, and/or wings, to permit preparation of a skeletal specimen.
notes: also known as a "schmoo", composition depends on specifications in dynamicProperties (e.g., may include legs/wings)

ornithology definition: A specimen consisting of the skin, skull, and bill.
A specimen consisting of the skin and feathers of the wing, often (but not always) including wing bones.
Tail specimens generally consist of the rectrices attached to skin and the pygostyle.
Specimen consists of a tail and a minimum of 1 wing
Specimen consisting of the bones and skin of the hind limb, generally with most or all muscle tissue removed.
The hindlimb, generally preserved as the tarsometatarsus and more extreme elements.
An individual feather, or set of feathers.
A thickened and more vascular portion of the abdominal skin that aids in incubating eggs
all bony elements within the body of the individual
notes: whole skeleton, trunk, or skull will be most common; list other possibilities (e.g., tibiotarsus) in dynamic properties

ornithology definition: cranium and mandible
partial specimen of the skull, often lacking, e.g., extreme of the maxilla
Partial skeleton or particular bones, but not the skull, trunk skeleton, or entire skeleton
the enlarged portion in the middle of the syrinx in some species of Anseriformes
notes: This particular syringeal element does not appear to be in Uberon

ornithology definition: check whether this exists as a bony element
notes: This particular element does not appear to be in Uberon

preservation type: DEFAULT = "FLUID"; when NOT in fluid, specify other (e.g., FREEZEDRIED)
ornithology definition: Entire body of a bird, including integument, musculature, and internal organs; note that individual parts may be missing owing to vagaries of preparation and collection, or of subsequent study and dissection.
Some subset of the whole body, often lacking head or limbs, as a consequence of preserving other parts of the body.

notes: in birds, roughly equivalent to gizzard, as that is the muscular part that is enlarged and that is frequently preserved as part of scientific collections of birds.

ornithology definition: Contents of the gizzard of a bird, which may include gastroliths and food items in various stages of digestion.
A pouched enlargement of the gullet that serves as a receptacle for food and for its preliminary maceration.
The contents of the crop.
A bolus of material, generally from prey items, that is preserved for study for diet analysis.
Feces.
notes: Is this a term used in ornithology and for bird specimens?

ornithology definition: The structure from the trachea, bronchi, and bronchioles that forms the airways that supply air to the lungs, including the syrinx (sensu stricto), which is the sound production organ in most birds.
Stones held in the digestive tract.
Airway connecting the mouth to the bronchi.
A muscular organ in the floor of the mouth.
A suite of bony elements lying just below the tongue, and often preserved with the tongue.
The cranium and associated integument, musculature, and nervous and digestive system elements.
The hindlimb, generally preserved as the tarsometatarsus and more extreme elements.
The center of the nervous system, held within the cranium.
Anatomical system which consists of organs and tissues associated with sexual reproduction of the organism.[AAO]
A collection of internal organs, generally including the GI tract, liver, spleen, kidneys, etc.
The tube that connects the mouth to the cloaca, with associated organs and modifications.
The true stomach of a bird that is situated between the crop and gizzard.
An external anatomical feature that include maxilla, mandible, ramphotheca, etc.

notes: could call "anatomical" specimen, although skeletons are that also. whole body, trunk, or stomach will be most common; list other possibilities (e.g., head) in dynamic properties

ornithology definition: The sensory organ that detects light.
The calcareous shell and ovum or embryo that it contains.
Diverse constructions made by birds for the purpose of holding and protecting eggs.

A material sample dedicated to a single taxon, often chemically or physically treated to preserve biomolecules from degrading. May contain tissue/DNA of other taxa, e.g. endosymbionts, pathogens, destruents
notes: heart, liver, and muscle will be the most frequent, along with unspecified; list other tissue types (kidney, lung, brain, eye, intestine, etc.) in dynamic properties

ornithology definition: A muscular organ that impulses blood through the circulatory system.
A visceral organ that aids in metabolism.
Muscle tissue that is generally under voluntary control, and that connects bones, tendons, and ligaments.
A fluid that flows in the circulatory system and carries oxygen to key body organs.
An organ that functions to produce urine.
Respiratory organ that serves to oxygenate the blood.
The center of the nervous system, held within the cranium.
The sensory organ that detects light.
Reproductive organ that produces and releases eggs (ovary) or sperm (testis).
A gonad of a male animal that produces and releases sperm.
The gonad of a female organism which contains germ cells.
Pedal digit skin and associated connective tissue.
The outer covering of the body that consists of dermis and epidermis.
Segment of the alimentary canal extending from the stomach to the cloaca.

notes: SUGGEST STRONGLY that this be under preservation method, as it does not refer to any part of a body.

ornithology definition: Common chamber into which the reproductive and excretory systems open.
notes: Often swabbed for virus or coccideal sampling.

ornithology definition: Chamber inside of the mouth from which the respiratory and digestive systems begin.
Orifice of the olfactory stystem
notes: Often flushed for sampling for XXXXX.

ornithology definition: DNA extracted from some tissue of the organism and held in a purified form.
Other organism living on or within the body of the bird.
Other organism living on the body of the bird.
Other organism living in the body of the bird.
A skin abnormality ostensibly caused by an infection with a pox virus.
A mass of tissue that has grown abnormally out of proportion.
no information provided in the data record that is relevant to the question of body part

preservation type: refers media not explicitly referring to a body part
ornithology definition: use for digital media that do not refer to a particular body part
